						Creating Input Fields in Tkinter
						
To input data 
we use : Entry()

e = Entry(root)
e.pack()

Some parameters are :- 
1. width

e =Entry(root, width=50)

2. bg, fg, borderwidth

e = Entry(root, width=50, bg='blue', fg='white', borderwidth=5)

To get the data to the code from gui application. We use .get() method to do so.
e.get()

To put some default text inside the box then,
e.insert(0, "Enter Your Name :- ")
